comment: Millsap (ATL) hand checks Rudez (MIN) at the start of his drive, affecting his RSBQ.
LATR shows that Rudez (MIN) and Dieng (MIN) maintain legal guarding positions when defending Millsap (ATL) on his layup attempt.
Sefolosha (ATL) makes incidental hand contact to Wiggins' (MIN) body and arm that do not affect his RSBQ as he starts his drive.
RATR shows that Millsap (ATL) does not maintain a vertical position when defending Wiggins (MIN) on his shot attempt. Millsap's arms are not vertical when contact occurs.

Horford (ATL) sets a legal screen on LaVine (MIN). Since LaVine is stationary and Horford is in an area that could be visible to LaVine, Horford does not need to give him any room and he absorbs contact.
L-Slash shows Dieng (MIN) cleanly strips the ball from Teague (ATL).
RATR shows Horford (ATL) loses the ball with no contact from LaVine (MIN).
LHH shows Sefolosha (ATL) cleanly blocks LaVine's (MIN) shot attempt, making incidental contact prior to his upward shooting motion when he turns around.
Minnesota regains possession after the blocked shot attempt and commits a 24 second violation.
Horford (ATL) maintains a legal guarding position as he defends Wiggins' (MIN) shot attempt.
Wiggins (MIN) and Millsap (ATL) make incidental contact in their attempt to secure the rebound.
R-Slash shows that LaVine (MIN) makes contact with Teague's (ATL) head on his drive to the rim, but before he begins an upward shooting motion.
Millsap (ATL) commits a take foul on Martin (MIN).
Wiggins (MIN) maintains a vertical and legal guarding position during Millsap's (ATL) shot attempt.
